Vice President Biden will be attending the official kickoff event for the restoration and renovation of the Wilmington Train Station on May 4th. He will be joined by Governor Jack Markell, Senators Tom Carper and Ted Kaufman, Congressman Mike Castle, and Mayor Jim Baker. The event will highlight the progress made in the restoration project, which has been funded by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009. The Vice President, who has been a daily Amtrak commuter from the Wilmington Train Station for over 36 years, will discuss how the funding from the Recovery Act will help repair and update critical infrastructure needs. The event is open to the press, and media details are provided for those planning to cover the event.